Turkey to Tax Electric Cars Up to 15 Percent, Haberturk Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-02-26T12:34:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-26/turkey-to-tax-electric-cars-up-to-15-percent-haberturk-says.html
The Turkish government plans to
impose a tax of between 3 percent and 15 percent on electric car
sales,  Haberturk  reported, citing Finance Minister  Mehmet Simsek .  The tax will be 3 percent for car with 85 kilowatts (114
horsepower) of engine power, 7 percent for cars with an engine
power between 85 kilowatts to 120 kilowatts and 15 percent for
those above 120 kilowatts, Simsek said, according to the
Istanbul-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 